message: Editor: Fixed PointLight not moving. Fixed Object3D panel changing when camera moving.
Editor: Changed object picking logic. Objects need to be clicked first before moving. Hopefully this will avoid mistakingly moved object and will make undo less needed :P
Editor: Trying OrbitControls instead. TrackballControls can be a bit of a pain...
SoftwareRenderer: Moving the rectangle reset to the clear. Fixes the glitches on the editor. But I don't remember what the logic of this is. I'll have to have a closer look later.
Fixed vertex normals and UVs for CircleGeometry
Updated OculusRiftEffect. Now it should work with the original OculusRift
update convert_obj_three.py docstring with current loader interface
Small tweaks to CanvasRenderer, SVGRenderer and SoftwareRenderer.
Replaced all http://mrdoob.github.com/three.js/ instances with http://threejs.org/.
Fixed bug in Phong shader when using normal maps with derivative tangents
Editor: Moved exporting stuff out of Viewport.
Deprecated parameters.clearColor and parameters.clearAlpha from WebGLRenderer contructor. Added missing setClearColor to other renderers. Updated editor.
Added fromArray and toArray to Quaternion.
SceneLoader2: Support files with no geometries and/or materials.
Optimized the PCF shadow map filtering to use vector comparisons.
Improved minecraft examples. Using atlas instead of MeshFaceMaterial. It's still being rendered in 2 drawcalls though (big geometry).
THREE.extend again breaking things. It happens on a project I'm working on, not sure still why. I guess this approach is safer.
Renamed Matrix4's copyRotation to extractRotation back. As per @WestLangley suggestion in #3220.
Helpers: Using matrixWorld instead of just position. Some bits to figure out still...
Reduced poly count from dynamic cubemap example.
Switched to FlyControls in LOD example.
Docs: HemisphereLight: Renamed hex to skyColor and groundColor. Closes #3215.
SceneLoader2/SceneExporter2: Last minute format change. User level shouldn't notice it.
Editor: Enable recursivity when looking for the object child. Fixes problem of not being able to add children with more than one level of hierarchy.
Editor: Fixed Object3D panel being visible at startup.
TextGeometry being a bit more user friendly. Fixes #3238.
Editor: Moving delete shortcut handling outside of Viewport. Also showing Scene on top of scene graph.
Editor: Object can now change parents.
Added getObjectById to Object3D. Renamed getChildByName to getObjectByName. I'm undecided about this change. Not sure if getObject* is better than getChild*.
Editor: Simplified fog panel visibility code.
Use Shader Defines for Bokeh Shader 2
Adding a more realistic + configurable Bokeh Shader to examples (#3182)
Add a THREE loader for PLY ASCII files.
SceneLoader2/SceneExporter2: Start to ignore values that are equal to default.
Editor: Better handling of json models.
optimize application of scale in Matrix4.makeFromPosition*Scale() - no ifs and fewer multiplies.
Editor: Validate userData JSON on key up. @sole I hope this solution does the trick for you too ;)
add backwards compatibility stubs with deprecated warnings for Matrix4.setRotationFromEuler/setRotationFromQuaternion/compose
Editor: Added PlaneGeometry and CubeGeometry parameters panel.
Editor: Built in geometries parameter editor starting to work.
Hacked WebGLRenderer to allow changing geometry of object.
UI.js: Added textTransform and .remove() to Panel.
Blender addons have a new path on Linux.
optimize Matrix4.compose to remove temporaries and unnecessary matrix multiplication.
simplify Object3D matrix construction via use of Matrix4.compose().
Matrix4.setRotationFrom* -> Matrix4.makeRotationFrom* and make them fully destructive as they are already partially destructive.
SceneLoader: Handling geometry and material names.
SceneExporter2/SceneLoader2: Improved SpotLight and HemisphereLight support.
Removed yet some more .translate() and .rotateByAxis() instances. See #3185.
Added MaterialLoader and MaterialExporter. Base code by now...
Editor: Implemented localStorage. Thanks to @sole for the suggestion!

SceneExporter2: Added handling of built-in geometries. The problem now is that JSONLoader returns geometry/materials. By now I'll ignore the materials but I'll need to think how to solve that eventually.
Editor: Add scene children instead of scene.

Added "lower level" immediate rendering functionality. The existing mechanism requires modification of the WebGLRenderer for different objects. The new implementation leaves the current MarchingCubes immediate renderer intact but checks for existence of a immediateRenderCallback member function of the object. If found, that object is added to the scene.__webglObjectsImmediate array. The program, webgl context, and frustum are currently passed into the callback, putting al rendering responsibility at the implementing object. This may break the Three.js abstraction somewhat, but allows "power users" to do some funky webgl stuff while still relying on the Three.js framework for the rest of the scene...
